<http://drug.uk/interaction/ciclosporin-yellow-fever-vaccine> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://drug.uk/model/DrugInteraction> .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/015febf5-9bf1-48ca-8c91-997bc4a9a502> <http://drug.uk/model/evidence> "Study" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/015febf5-9bf1-48ca-8c91-997bc4a9a502> <http://drug.uk/model/severity> "Severe" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/015febf5-9bf1-48ca-8c91-997bc4a9a502> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Ciclosporin increases the concentration of Tacrolimus. Manufacturer advises avoid.  " .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/015febf5-9bf1-48ca-8c91-997bc4a9a502> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://drug.uk/model/InteractionDetail> .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/01ebefa1-6850-4bf9-a070-b28724da5009> <http://drug.uk/model/severity> "Normal" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/01ebefa1-6850-4bf9-a070-b28724da5009> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Both Ciclosporin and Potassium chloride can increase the risk of hyperkalaemia (hyperkalaemia is particularly notable when ACE inhibitors or angiotensin-II receptor antagonists are given with spironolactone or eplerenone)." .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/01ebefa1-6850-4bf9-a070-b28724da5009> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://drug.uk/model/InteractionDetail> .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/02365991-8082-48b0-815c-173ae623637b> <http://drug.uk/model/evidence> "Theoretical" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/02365991-8082-48b0-815c-173ae623637b> <http://drug.uk/model/severity> "Severe" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/02365991-8082-48b0-815c-173ae623637b> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Dengue vaccine is predicted to increase the risk of generalised infection (possibly life-threatening) when given with Ciclosporin. UKHSA advises avoid (refer to Green Book).  " .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/02365991-8082-48b0-815c-173ae623637b> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://drug.uk/model/InteractionDetail> .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/030df14d-b286-41eb-9e92-f6a66e81c13a> <http://drug.uk/model/evidence> "Theoretical" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/030df14d-b286-41eb-9e92-f6a66e81c13a> <http://drug.uk/model/severity> "Moderate" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/030df14d-b286-41eb-9e92-f6a66e81c13a> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Ivacaftor is predicted to increase the exposure to Ciclosporin. Manufacturer advises caution.  " .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/030df14d-b286-41eb-9e92-f6a66e81c13a> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://drug.uk/model/InteractionDetail> .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/03332dc1-8f58-4b11-a2d3-6e081a7ef141> <http://drug.uk/model/severity> "Normal" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/03332dc1-8f58-4b11-a2d3-6e081a7ef141> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Both Ciclosporin and Sulfasalazine can increase the risk of nephrotoxicity." .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/03332dc1-8f58-4b11-a2d3-6e081a7ef141> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://drug.uk/model/InteractionDetail> .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/038fd9cc-3fd1-4fca-9530-5c40f5387bc6> <http://drug.uk/model/evidence> "Theoretical" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/038fd9cc-3fd1-4fca-9530-5c40f5387bc6> <http://drug.uk/model/severity> "Moderate" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/038fd9cc-3fd1-4fca-9530-5c40f5387bc6> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Blinatumomab is predicted to transiently increase the exposure to Ciclosporin. Manufacturer advises monitor and adjust dose.  " .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/038fd9cc-3fd1-4fca-9530-5c40f5387bc6> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://drug.uk/model/InteractionDetail> .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/043777c2-d011-4fb8-9e72-46c93eaf3124> <http://drug.uk/model/evidence> "Theoretical" .
<http://drug.uk/interaction/detail/043777c2-d011-4fb8-9e72-46c93eaf3124> <http://drug.uk/model/severity> "Moderate" .
